                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "People in the concrete operational stage can think abstractly, while those in the formal operational stage think primarily in discrete units."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "People in the concrete operational stage focus more on yes/no scenarios, whereas those in the formal operational stage can envision a compromise."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "People in the concrete operational stage are in the process of developing language skills, while those in the formal operational stage are associating language skills with symbols."
